cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper heavily relies on computer vision techniques to extract visual information from images of jewelry items, which is then used in conjunction with other attributes to predict their resale prices. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an AI system that autonomously assesses the resale prices of secondhand jewelry items without the need for professional knowledge. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper employs state-of-the-art multimodal deep neural networks to achieve a practical performance level in predicting resale prices. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper deals with the task of predicting the resale prices of secondhand jewelry items, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper uses a multimodal approach combining visual information and attributes of the product to obtain fine-grained representations of secondhand jewelry items.
